Bypass Certificate Pinning Using Frida
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Understand SSL certificate pinning mechanisms in mobile applications
Install and configure Frida for dynamic instrumentation
Write Frida scripts to bypass common certificate pinning implementations
Intercept and analyze SSL/TLS traffic from Android applications
Automate certificate pinning bypass using Python and Frida
Prerequisites
Students should have:

Basic understanding of SSL/TLS protocols and certificate validation
Familiarity with JavaScript and Python programming
Knowledge of Android application architecture
Experience with Linux command-line interfaces
Lab Environment
Your cloud machine includes:

Frida - Dynamic instrumentation toolkit (pre-installed)
Python 3 with frida-tools library
Android Debug Bridge (ADB)
Android emulator with test application
Burp Suite Community Edition
Text editors (nano, vim)
All tools are pre-configured and ready to use.

